      • canInvoke

        public boolean canInvoke(javax.management.MBeanServer mbeanServer,
                         javax.management.ObjectName objectName,
                         java.lang.String methodName,
                         java.lang.String[] signature)
                  throws java.io.IOException
        Return true if the method on the MBean with the specified signature can be invoked.
        Parameters:
        mbeanServer - The MBeanServer where the object is registered.
        objectName - The MBean ObjectName.
        methodName - The name of the method.
        signature - The signature of the method.
        Returns:
        True if the method can be invoked, false else. Note that if a method name or signature is provided that does not exist on the MBean, the behaviour of this method is undefined. In other words, if you ask whether a method that does not exist can be invoked, the method may return true but actually invoking that method will obviously not work.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If the invocation fails.
